race.comment: Race has been completely turned on its head after scratchings of three runners who looked the likely main chances. Suspect NARALINGA (1) is the main beneficiary. Won first up at Mt Gambier where he settled back and ran on. Fitter and out of the main chances is the one who has best proven himself outside of maiden company. Will settle back in the small field and suspect he can round them up. ZAMORA (5) ran a big race at odds first up when placing at Donald before dropping in trip and saluting at Gunbower. Tougher here however has clearly returned in great order. SHOUT ME (6) is relatively lightly raced and could bounce back off a poor one last time. The start prior shed his maiden tag when leading throughout at Hamilton. BRISEIS ECLIPSE (9) another last start maiden winner.
